Data Collection, Sharing and Privacy
Anti-Eviction Mapping Project (AEMP)

Our site serves as a data aggregator to support housing justice movements against Landlord Tech. We only collect information Landlord Tech deployment, and share this information
with community organizations and research groups working for housing justice.

1) The data we collect and display on the map is public. The goal of our data collection is to support social movements, housing justice organizations, and research groups working in solidarity initiatives to address the challenges of
Landlord Tech.

2) We privilege information security of our users and their data. No information about access to our website (i.e., your IP address) will be collected. We do not collect and store personal information or personal identifiers of any type, other than what is entered in our survey. We encourage users to preferably use the Tor Browser if they are interested in submitted data anonymously. If you do submit your name or contact information so that we can follow up with you, we will not publish any of this identifying information on our map.

3) In order to support housing justice action, we make our map data available to social movements and research groups. Contact us to discuss how to obtain our public data in an open format.

4) Private and sensitive information collected through interviews will not be aggregated in the public database of this site and will not be made publicly available without prior authorization from the person or group interviewed.

5) Our group reviews the contributions made on the site and removes inappropriate content regularly. Our group is not responsible, however, for data sent by our users. We do not provide any guarantees about the information provided on the site.


This document was prepared by the AEMP 
